cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on solving the problem of prepositional phrase (PP) attachments in English. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm based on dual decomposition, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also involves experiments and evaluation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with language translation, which could make cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
